<br>
Now... the question... is she taking things way too far, or does she have a valid point?<br>
<br>
When I think about it, I kind of mutilate the pledge of allegiance myself.  We say it every Monday in advisory, and another friend and I have been slowly whittling it down to what we really believe.  Here's what we've got...<br>
<br>
&quot;I pledge allegiance to the republic for which it stands, one nation, under God, with liberty and justice for most.&quot;  The rest we just stay silent on, and nobody notices.  Of course, we only do that in fun, and my other anti-pledge friend is really serious about it.<br>
<br>
School spirit... patriotism... conflicting Christianity?<br>
<br>
~Jaguwolf<br>
